# Task docs (biotastic)

Before **non-trivial** work (new behaviour, multi-file changes, security/data model):

1. Skim **`docs/tasks/completed.md`**. Open any matching files under **`docs/tasks/done/`** for context.
2. For **in-progress multi-slice work**, open the task’s **handoff** if present: **`docs/tasks/open/<slug>-handoff.md`** (see **`docs/tasks/README.md`** — slice completion handoff). Use it to continue from the last GREEN slice without re-deriving context. If the user maintains **`docs/tasks/CURRENT_HANDOFF.md`**, read that **first** and follow its links to the active handoff and task (see **`docs/tasks/README.md`** — “Resume in a new chat”).
3. **Task-first** (when the user asks for it, e.g. “task first” / “create the task first”): add **`docs/tasks/open/<slug>.md`** from **`docs/tasks/TEMPLATE.md`** before editing **`grails-app/`** (and related app code). When done, move the file to **`docs/tasks/done/`**, update **`docs/tasks/completed.md`**, per **`docs/tasks/README.md`**.
4. **After a TDD slice reaches GREEN:** add or append a slice section to **`docs/tasks/open/<slug>-handoff.md`** using **`docs/tasks/HANDOFF-TEMPLATE.md`**, and link it from the task file’s **Links** section. **Only when** the user is using the **`CURRENT_HANDOFF.md` workflow:** no extra update is required per slice unless they switched tasks; they repoint **`CURRENT_HANDOFF.md`** when starting a different task or clear it when work is idle.
5. Skip (3)–(4) for trivial edits or if the user says to skip task files.

If rules were not in context, still follow (1)–(4) when the user mentions tasks or **`docs/tasks`** (handoffs and post-GREEN slice notes when doing TDD slices).
